  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Partnership for Empowerment of Vulnerable Girls and Women in Urban Slums of Kampala City  (PEVUS)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Around 20,000 girls under the age of 18 are sex workers in Kampala&#x2019;s slums, some as young as 13, many having been trafficked from rural areas. This can lead to high rates of HIV/AIDS, substance abuse, mental health disorders and exposure to violence from clients or the police. This project supports sexually exploited young women, helping them find less risky alternatives to make a living. Rehabilitation and vocational training helps participants develop the skills and confidence to find employment or start a business. The whole community benefits from improved access to services for sexual and reproductive health, and the project ensures both local communities and those in positions of authority acknowledge the importance of protecting the rights of young women forced into sex work.</narrative>
  </description>
